OL,3,CPreston Davey murder trial hears
OL,4,Cdefence barristers' closing speeches
OL,6,FShe suggested McGowan-Fazakerley was
OL,7,Fat work and "notably absent" at key
OL,8,Fmoments, with "parts of the jigsaw"
OL,9,Fkept from him.
OL,11,FMs Whyte told the jury: "It is clear,
OL,12,Fwhatever happened, that one of them
OL,13,Fput legitimate trust in the other.
OL,15,F"If you trust and love someone then
OL,16,Fyou are the last person to suspect.
OL,18,F"He too, I'm going to suggest, wants
OL,19,Fto know the truth."
OL,26,@oD@MOUoD@\O]pD@OOUpD@cO]sD@YOUwD@AOUzD@
OL,26,AAOU{D@SO]
