OL,3,CPreston Davey murder trial hears
OL,4,Cdefence barristers' closing speeches
OL,6,FShe said McGowan-Fazakerley had
OL,7,Finitially believed Preston had died
OL,8,Ffrom secondary drowning possibly
OL,9,Fcomplicated by a chest infection.
OL,11,FDescribing the defendant as a "quiet,
OL,12,Fdecent, caring man" but with little
OL,13,Fexperience of caring for children, he
OL,14,Ftrusted his partner and the "battery
OL,15,Fof professionals" who also saw Preston
OL,16,Fin the weeks before his death.
OL,18,FMs Whyte added: "Preston was a highly
OL,19,Fvisible child. No-one was hiding him.
OL,26,@sD@_OUtD@SO]vD@]OUwD@QO]zD@QOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
